Q635:
In this study, we will ask you to answer a few questions regarding your views. You must be over 18 years of age to participate. The following information is important for your informed consent. The project is titled “Donors” (Protocol Number: AAAV7598) and is being run by Professor Mohamed Hussein at Columbia University. The study is done to understand how people perceive others.



Payment: You will be compensated at a rate dislayed on the survey platform. This survey is expected to take less than 5 minutes to complete. Your payment will be provided to you through the survey platform you used to access this survey.



Risk & Benefits: Please note that there is no potential risk involved other than a potential breach of confidentiality. The benefits which may reasonably be expected from this study are knowledge about how adults process information and make decisions accordingly. The following people and/or agencies will be able to look at and copy your research records: (1) The investigator, study staff, and other professionals who may be evaluating

the study, (2) Authorities from Columbia University, including the Institutional Review Board (‘IRB’). An IRB is a committee organized to protect the rights and welfare of people involved in research.



Please make sure you read and understand the questions carefully before answering. There are no right or wrong answers, so feel free to report your answers openly and truthfully. Participation is completely voluntary, and you are free to choose whether to withdraw from the study at any time without penalty or consequences of any kind. All information that you provide will be treated confidentially and all questions are anonymous. Furthermore, we will keep the data in a password-locked local device of the researcher for security. CU Human Research Protection Office may obtain access to the data collected for this study.



If you have any questions about this study, you can contact mh4547@gsb.columbia.edu. Please write down this contact information or print this consent document before proceeding to the study so that you can contact the researcher should any questions or concerns arise during your participation in the study. Moreover, if at any time you have specific questions or concerns about your rights or welfare as a study participant, contact the Columbia University Morningside Human Research Protection Office (HRPO) at 212-305-5883 or email askirb@columbia.edu.



By clicking “I agree” below, you acknowledge that you understand the procedures described above, you have reviewed this information and any questions you have about it have been answered, you understand that you are not giving up any legal rights you are otherwise entitled to, you are at least 18 years old, and you agree to participate in this study.
